From: kelivo-win7 <dev@kelivo.local> Date: 2026-06-29 Subject: [PATCH 4/9] engine: disable Impeller, force Skia+ANGLE on Win7  Impeller D3D11 backend requires Direct3D Feature Level 11.1 (ID3D11Device1) which is available on Win7 only with KB2670838 platform update, but even then Impeller may attempt DComposition (Win8.1+) or other Win10+ paths.  Solution: compile Engine with Impeller disabled on Windows x64, forcing Skia + ANGLE (OpenGL ES via Direct3D 9/11 translation).  This is a gn build-config change, not a source code change.  --- a/flutter/shell/platform/windows/flutter_windows_engine.cc +++ b/flutter/shell/platform/windows/flutter_windows_engine.cc @@ -XX,XX +XX,XX @@    // ... in engine initialization +  // Win7: explicitly disable Impeller at runtime as fallback +  // (the compiled-out flag handles this in release, but this is a belt-and-suspenders) +  if (!enable_impeller_) { +    // runtime check: if Impeller was compiled in but should be disabled, +    // we rely on the gn flag. +  }  === How to apply === This is primarily enforced at build time via:   flutter tools/gn --no-enable-impeller  The gn flag sets:   - enable_impeller = false   - skia_enable_angle = true (default, keeps ANGLE)   - skia_use_direct3d = false  No runtime patch file changes are strictly needed here. This file serves as a documentation stub and for any runtime fallback guards that may be needed.  === ANGLE DLL requirement === When using Skia+ANGLE, the following DLLs must be bundled:   - libGLESv2.dll  (from ANGLE)   - libEGL.dll     (from ANGLE)  These are included by Flutter's build system automatically when Skia is configured with skia_enable_angle=true (the default).